# 00-core-project-rules.mdc

## Purpose
This repository must stay secure, maintainable, readable, and cohesive.
Prefer small, well-scoped changes over broad rewrites.

## General behavior
- Before making changes, inspect the surrounding patterns and follow the existing architecture.
- Prefer modifying existing abstractions over creating parallel patterns.
- Do not introduce new libraries unless clearly justified.
- Keep changes minimal, explicit, and easy to review.
- If a task is ambiguous, prefer the least risky implementation that aligns with current project conventions.

## Project consistency
- Follow existing naming, folder, and component patterns.
- Reuse shared utilities, components, and helpers before creating new ones.
- Keep code style consistent with the repository, not personal preference.
- Do not duplicate logic that can be extracted into a shared utility.

## Change discipline
- Do not change unrelated files.
- Do not silently remove functionality to make code compile.
- Preserve backward compatibility unless the task explicitly allows breaking changes.
- If making a breaking change, update all affected references and documentation.

## Validation
- After meaningful code changes, run the relevant formatter, linter, type checker, and tests.
- Prefer the smallest relevant test scope first, then broader validation if needed.
